Change 890581003 by ajiteshp@ajiteshp:jetski-bug2code-481979358-9cfb1f08:71792:citc on 2026/03/27 12:21:21 *pending*

	[DO NOT SUBMIT] Fix use-of-uninitialized-value error in memrefCopy.cpp under MSAN
	
	The memory initialization issue occurred because memref structures created inside uninstrumented MLIR generated functions do not populate MSAN shadow memory, triggering uninitialized read warnings at boundary code where MSan interceptors exist (like reading properties or `memcpy` calls in `memrefCopy.cpp` or printing debug results).
	
	This CL adds `__msan_unpoison` calls for the missing boundary arrays/structs, similar to upstream CRunnerUtils.cpp logic, to correctly mark memory as initialized for MSAN.
	
	This fixes the MSAN aborts reported in bug 481979358.
	
	
	This CL was generated by an MCP server owned by the Gemini CLI for Google team.
	See go/gemini-cli-install for more information.
	
